WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:14.514 --> 03:16.584
Let's go down.

03:27.154 --> 03:31.067
- You got some out. How many left?
- Three out, eight left.

03:31.154 --> 03:34.430
- Edgar's still the man?
- Edgar's the man.

03:34.514 --> 03:37.392
Edgar, l want to thank you
for letting these people go.

03:37.434 --> 03:41.222
Send out the others, and we can come
to a peaceful resolution.

03:41.274 --> 03:45.062
Get this straight. l don't trust you or
any agent of your occupation government.

03:45.114 --> 03:46.991
Listen to me
one more time.

03:47.034 --> 03:50.231
l have an order from the Citizens' Court
of South Dakota...

03:50.314 --> 03:52.782
to seize the ill-gotten assets
of this bank.

03:52.874 --> 03:56.583
Move your people away from here or
these bloodsuckers will burn in hell!

04:04.154 --> 04:06.031
They're gettin' ready
to come in.

04:06.114 --> 04:08.503
Let them come.

04:08.594 --> 04:10.983
- l have to go home.
- Get down!

04:11.074 --> 04:13.269
Please, let me go home.
Please, let me go home.

04:13.354 --> 04:16.426
- Get the fuck down!
- l just need to go home.

04:16.514 --> 04:19.074
When he says ''get down,''
just do it!

04:28.714 --> 04:30.784
Damn!

04:37.474 --> 04:40.705
l sure don't feel good.

04:40.754 --> 04:44.144
You said we were gonna be in and out of
here before anybody knew what hit 'em.

04:44.234 --> 04:47.306
You said they were
gonna back down.

04:47.354 --> 04:50.346
They ain't backin' down, Edgar.

04:50.394 --> 04:52.783
They got an army
out there.

04:52.874 --> 04:54.910
They're gonna come in here
and shoot all of us.

04:54.994 --> 04:57.064
God just wants His miracle
to be greater.

04:57.114 --> 05:00.504
God doesn't want your boys
to get killed, Edgar!

05:09.234 --> 05:11.907
We need more time,
you sons of bitches!

05:11.954 --> 05:14.024
You ain't in charge here.
So shut up!

05:14.074 --> 05:15.985
- They cut us off.
- We gotta go in.

05:16.074 --> 05:19.623
- We have a man in there.
He wants more time.
- Right.

05:19.714 --> 05:23.468
Undercover agent who isn't supposed
to be there in the first place.

05:23.554 --> 05:26.114
- We're goin' in.
- Let me try 'em on the bullhorn.

05:26.194 --> 05:28.105
- lf they come back to me--
- You've got three minutes.

05:31.554 --> 05:33.385
This is Agent Blackwell,
Edgar.

05:33.474 --> 05:38.673
l need you to pick up
the telephone.

05:38.754 --> 05:42.827
- l need to talk with you.
- We can still walk out of here.

05:42.874 --> 05:45.342
You just gotta
stand up to him.

05:47.594 --> 05:51.712
Just tell him you wanna go home.
Can you do it?

05:51.794 --> 05:56.151
Edgar, please pick up
the phone. We can still work this out.

06:02.754 --> 06:06.269
Edgar, please pick up
the phone. We were doing well before.

06:06.354 --> 06:08.185
Sir?

06:08.274 --> 06:10.390
Peter's right.

06:10.474 --> 06:14.228
lt's not like you said
it was going to be.

06:16.594 --> 06:18.425
l wanna go home.

06:31.634 --> 06:35.388
Edgar,
the boy's right.

06:35.474 --> 06:37.385
- Traitor.
- Daddy.
- Shut up, lsaac.

06:37.434 --> 06:39.948
- Let me call 'em on the telephone.
- We don't need him.

06:40.034 --> 06:42.502
- We can still walk out of here.
- Do it, Edgar!

06:42.554 --> 06:45.148
For your boys, do it!

06:56.154 --> 06:58.190
Get down! Get down!

07:01.394 --> 07:03.544
F.B.l.!
Get on the ground.

07:12.674 --> 07:14.904
Go, go, go!

07:14.994 --> 07:16.825
Daddy!

07:18.354 --> 07:20.106
Stay down!
Don't move.

07:20.194 --> 07:24.506
- Don't move, goddamn it!
- l'm F.B.l. F.B.l.!
Get off me, asshole!

07:24.594 --> 07:27.427
- Tell your men to hold their fire.
- Peter.

07:27.474 --> 07:29.783
- Peter.
- James?

07:29.874 --> 07:32.752
James, keep your head down!
Where are you?

07:32.794 --> 07:35.627
- Peter!
- No! No! No!

07:35.674 --> 07:39.030
Hold your fire!
No! No!

07:40.314 --> 07:41.952
Damn it!

07:44.634 --> 07:47.467
Goddamn it!

07:47.514 --> 07:49.391
Shoot! Shoot!

07:49.434 --> 07:54.747
Get a med tech in here!
Get a med tech in here, goddamn it!

07:54.834 --> 07:57.029
Don't talk.
Don't talk.

07:57.074 --> 07:59.463
Come on now, goddamn it!

07:59.554 --> 08:01.909
Get a med tech in here!

08:06.074 --> 08:07.632
He's dead.

08:15.514 --> 08:17.391
Who said ''go''?

08:19.354 --> 08:21.072
Who's the S.A.C.?

08:21.154 --> 08:23.952
Hartley.

08:27.474 --> 08:29.351
Hartley!

08:30.674 --> 08:33.631
Special Agent Hartley!

08:33.714 --> 08:36.592
Hartley! Did you hear me ask
for more time?

08:36.634 --> 08:39.831
- Get your hands off me.
- Did you hear me ask for more time?

08:39.914 --> 08:42.746
- You're out of line, Jeffries.
- l'm out of line? l'm out of line?

08:42.833 --> 08:47.703
Did l just massacre
five fuckin' people? Huh? Did l?

08:47.794 --> 08:52.470
Three seconds, Hartley,
l was gonna walk 'em all out alive.

08:52.554 --> 08:54.272
Massacre.

08:54.354 --> 08:56.822
They were just kids.

08:58.994 --> 09:00.871
Just kids.

09:02.114 --> 09:05.789
l report to Washington
just like you do, Jeffries.

09:57.434 --> 10:01.393
Right on Western.
Left on Belmont.

10:01.474 --> 10:04.272
- Hey, Simon, l have a surprise for you.
- Right on Halsted.

10:04.354 --> 10:08.427
- Left on Fullerton.
- You're giving some good directions.

10:08.514 --> 10:12.109
Look. l have something
very, very special.

10:12.194 --> 10:15.106
You like these puzzles,
don't ya?

10:15.154 --> 10:18.305
Uh-huh. Okay,
but not yet, Simon.

10:18.354 --> 10:22.666
lf l give you the puzzle book,
l want you to join in with
the rest of the class, okay?

10:31.314 --> 10:33.191
That's great.

10:33.234 --> 10:35.987
lt's time to join
the group now, okay?

10:41.194 --> 10:43.025
Good morning, Simon.

10:43.114 --> 10:44.991
Good morning, teacher.

10:45.074 --> 10:47.634
Look at me.

10:49.274 --> 10:51.788
Good morning, teacher.

11:09.194 --> 11:12.345
l better not beat you.
l only accept cash.

11:21.114 --> 11:24.743
- How are you?
- Well, another day at the office.

11:24.794 --> 11:27.433
- You ready?
- Yeah.

11:27.474 --> 11:30.227
All right,
let's talk about it.

11:31.474 --> 11:33.988
Agent Jeffries here
to see you, Chief.

11:42.874 --> 11:46.662
The psychologist wrote
''delusional paranoia''...

11:46.754 --> 11:49.712
in capital letters
across the bottom of your file.

11:49.754 --> 11:53.872
- So, am l fired?
- No, you're not fired.

11:56.354 --> 12:00.063
- But l can't put you undercover
anymore. That's over.
- What do they expect me to do?

12:00.114 --> 12:03.504
- To do your job.
- l work undercover. That's my job.

12:03.594 --> 12:06.506
- You have a new job now.
- And what is that?

12:06.554 --> 12:09.864
Sitting on a wire,
stakeouts, log tapes.

12:09.914 --> 12:12.382
- A little public relations.
- Fourteen years on the job,
and that's all it means?

12:12.434 --> 12:15.426
l've gotta sit
on a wire with some rookie listening
to a housewife order groceries?

12:15.474 --> 12:18.193
- All you had to do
was keep your mouth shut.
- All l did was tell the truth.

12:18.274 --> 12:21.232
- Act like you belong on the
same team as the rest of us.
- What team?

12:21.314 --> 12:24.112
That bunch of suits sitting behind a
desk trying to justify their existence?

12:24.154 --> 12:27.305
- Like me. ls that what you're saying?
- l don't know, Joe.

12:27.354 --> 12:30.232
- Why didn't you say one thing
to back me up?
- Because you were wrong!

12:30.314 --> 12:32.623
- l wasn't wrong!
- You were dead wrong.

12:32.714 --> 12:35.706
Two teenage kids in cold blood,
and you know it.

12:35.794 --> 12:39.070
- They were goddamn bank robbers,
for Christ's sake!
- They were kids.

12:39.154 --> 12:41.907
Will you forget
about South Dakota?

12:41.994 --> 12:45.066
Forget who's right and who's wrong.
This is one of the best undercover guys.

12:47.234 --> 12:49.589
How could l forget that?

12:52.914 --> 12:54.825
Sit down, Art.

13:03.274 --> 13:06.346
Sometimes...
you got somethin'.

13:07.474 --> 13:10.432
lt's... magic.

13:12.274 --> 13:14.185
Then it goes away.

13:14.234 --> 13:16.111
You had it.

13:17.314 --> 13:19.464
But the magic's gone.

13:21.234 --> 13:25.386
They told you to break my balls,
and see if you could get me to quit.

13:25.434 --> 13:27.504
l'm not gonna make it easy
for you.

13:27.594 --> 13:31.109
You want me to sit on a wire,
l'll do it.

13:31.154 --> 13:34.669
You want me to chase
file applicants, l'll do that.

13:34.714 --> 13:36.591
Take your best shot.

13:36.634 --> 13:39.307
Check your mailbox
for your new assignments.

14:00.234 --> 14:02.668
Hey, Simon, we're here.

14:28.474 --> 14:30.704
Mommy, Simon is home.

14:30.794 --> 14:33.388
Look at me.

14:33.474 --> 14:35.305
Hi, Mom.

14:35.354 --> 14:38.426
Hi, honey. l missed you.
Come on inside.

15:19.834 --> 15:22.394
Be careful.

15:22.474 --> 15:24.271
lt's very hot.

15:24.314 --> 15:26.464
Sip it slowly.

15:28.394 --> 15:30.385
Daddy'll be home soon.

15:30.474 --> 15:34.069
And when you finish that,
you can wait for him up in your room.

17:18.034 --> 17:20.673
Congratulations.
You've reached the Puzzle Center.

17:20.753 --> 17:22.585
For solving one
of our master puzzles...

17:22.674 --> 17:25.472
you've won a subscription
to the magazine of your choice.

17:25.554 --> 17:27.464
Can l please have your name,
address and telephone number?

17:27.554 --> 17:29.624
You are...

17:29.714 --> 17:31.670
a stranger.

17:31.754 --> 17:36.908
Excuse me. This the Puzzle Center.
Where did you get this number?

17:36.994 --> 17:40.873
Puzzle nine-nine.

17:40.914 --> 17:43.144
What did you just say?
Who is this?

17:43.234 --> 17:45.065
Simon,
put down the phone.

17:45.114 --> 17:47.469
Simon, Simon, wait a second.
Please don't hang--

17:55.794 --> 17:58.149
Come on, come on.

17:59.754 --> 18:01.153
Figures.

18:01.234 --> 18:03.065
See if they correlate.

18:03.154 --> 18:06.544
lf they don't, you may have lost some
bytes in the transfer, lost a keyword.

18:06.634 --> 18:09.751
You won't be able
to defractionate. Yeah?

18:09.834 --> 18:11.950
- Are you scrambled?
- Give me a break, Leo. l'm busy.

18:11.994 --> 18:15.066
lt's Mercury, Dean. Somebody just walked
on water. You have to get up here now.

18:20.914 --> 18:26.386
- What did you just say?
- You are a stranger.

18:26.474 --> 18:29.671
- Who is this?
- Simon, put down the phone.

18:29.714 --> 18:32.990
Simon, Simon, wait a second.
Please don't hang--

18:34.034 --> 18:35.911
Who is that?

18:37.434 --> 18:39.629
Listen to the timbre
of his voice.

18:39.714 --> 18:43.263
lt's a child.
That had to be his mother.

18:43.314 --> 18:45.225
Right. lt's just
some rug rat...

18:45.274 --> 18:48.346
drooling over the phone,
punching numbers, like a random thing.

18:48.434 --> 18:50.265
Huh?

18:51.314 --> 18:53.350
We're not that lucky.

18:56.354 --> 18:58.868
- We have to call Kudrow.
- What? Dean, what?

18:58.954 --> 19:01.184
No, no, no.
We don't have to call anybody.

19:01.234 --> 19:04.829
All we gotta do is an analysis,
and give him a report when he gets back.

19:04.914 --> 19:08.111
- That's it!
- Do you understand what just happened?

19:08.194 --> 19:11.789
We have to call him now
or he's gonna say we tried to hide it.

19:20.874 --> 19:23.627
- Morning, sir.
- Good morning, Marine.

19:23.714 --> 19:27.150
l've got an urgent message
for Lieutenant Colonel Kudrow.

19:27.194 --> 19:30.630
Mercury is already
operational in most of our com centers.

19:30.674 --> 19:33.632
And l'm here to confirm
everything you've already heard.

19:33.714 --> 19:37.548
Mercury is a quantum leap
in our communications security.

19:37.634 --> 19:40.626
And once we complete its installation
in all of our com centers...

19:40.714 --> 19:43.786
- it's going to be very hard
for our adversaries--
- And our allies.

19:43.834 --> 19:48.510
And our allies to compromise
our communications.

19:48.594 --> 19:51.062
An urgent message
for you, sir.

19:56.714 --> 19:58.545
lf you'll excuse me.

19:58.634 --> 20:02.752
-Mr. Johnson will continue the briefing.
-All right, gentlemen.

20:18.034 --> 20:19.865
lmpossible.

21:04.794 --> 21:08.503
- You're late.
- l wasn't when l started.

21:09.754 --> 21:11.949
Traffic was like mud.

21:11.994 --> 21:13.871
l oozed home.

21:17.394 --> 21:20.591
l told Simon
he could wait up for you.

21:20.634 --> 21:22.590
Simon, my man.

21:28.154 --> 21:31.669
l wonder where Simon is.

21:36.674 --> 21:39.188
Time for bed, Simon.

23:09.714 --> 23:13.946
-Send in Pedranski and Crandell, please.
- Yes, sir.

23:28.474 --> 23:31.989
Who needs a fix?
Double tall, double dark, double sweet.

23:32.074 --> 23:34.827
Double everything. l'm so glad l missed
the whole drug thing...

23:34.874 --> 23:37.627
so my body was virgin territory
for caffeine.

23:37.714 --> 23:42.026
lt makes me feel so Ricki Lake,
like l can talk to anybody.

23:42.074 --> 23:46.352
What can l say? l'm the Java Queen.
What's wrong?

23:47.394 --> 23:49.225
Kudrow wants to see me.

23:49.314 --> 23:53.102
Cool! Maybe you'll get
your own section.

23:53.194 --> 23:55.071
No. l, uh,
l screwed up.

23:55.154 --> 23:58.351
Well, just go in there
and throw him a Bart Simpson.

23:58.394 --> 24:00.271
Kudrow, dude, chill out.

24:00.354 --> 24:02.993
- lt was that way when l got there.
- Doh!

24:09.394 --> 24:11.544
Puzzle line?

24:11.634 --> 24:14.102
Puzzle line?

24:14.194 --> 24:17.027
Now, l've traveled 10,000 miles
in the past 24 hours.

24:17.074 --> 24:19.952
So l've had a lot of time to reflect
on this. Correct me if l'm wrong.

24:20.034 --> 24:25.062
But l believe neither one of you has
ever said the words ''puzzle line'' to me.

24:26.674 --> 24:30.826
Before Mercury went operational,
we ran a standard validation protocol.

24:30.914 --> 24:33.064
The works. Double sets of paired
Cray supercomputers...

24:33.154 --> 24:36.430
fricking velociraptor machines
chewing at Mercury 24 hours a day.

24:36.474 --> 24:38.032
Mercury came out unbent.

24:38.074 --> 24:41.066
Awesome, sir. lt was finally a code
that couldn't be broken.

24:41.154 --> 24:46.069
But there was one last thing
to check out. The, um... geek factor.

24:46.154 --> 24:49.590
Human beings will fool you sometimes.
We thought it important--

24:49.674 --> 24:54.304
We slipped a message
in one of those egghead word games.
We dared amateurs to crack it.

24:54.354 --> 24:57.073
- We were sure nobody would ever call.
- But somebody did.

24:59.954 --> 25:04.106
His name is Simon Lynch. He lives
in Chicago. He is nine years old.

25:04.194 --> 25:07.584
And he has deciphered a message written
in the most sophisticated code...

25:07.634 --> 25:09.750
the world has ever known...

25:09.834 --> 25:12.906
in a geek's
puzzle magazine.

25:12.994 --> 25:15.064
l don't recall
ever authorizing...

25:15.154 --> 25:17.873
anyone to put any message...

25:17.954 --> 25:19.945
into any magazine!

25:19.994 --> 25:24.033
That couldn't just happen.
A kid couldn't just pop it open.

25:24.114 --> 25:29.063
Not only is he nine years old,
he is handicapped. He is autistic.

25:29.114 --> 25:31.150
Yes, that explains it.

25:31.234 --> 25:34.192
So our $2 billion code
is an open book...

25:34.234 --> 25:36.429
- to people of diminished capacity?
- No, sir.

25:36.514 --> 25:39.551
Autism isn't synonymous
with diminished capacity.

25:39.634 --> 25:42.671
Autistic people are--
They're shut off.

25:42.714 --> 25:45.672
But it's not unusual
for an autistic person to be a savant.

25:45.714 --> 25:48.751
- Oh, a savant!
- He may not be able
to actually decipher the code.

25:48.794 --> 25:50.910
- lt might just appear to him.
- Right. He didn't calculate anything.

25:50.994 --> 25:54.748
He just saw it. Like those stupid
pictures at the mall. You stare at them.

25:54.834 --> 25:57.553
- All of a sudden you're looking
at the Statue of Liberty.
- Exactly.

25:57.634 --> 26:00.910
This is not a stupid picture
at the mall.

26:00.994 --> 26:03.064
This is national security.

26:05.674 --> 26:09.906
Looking at the best case scenario,
let's suppose the boy is unique...

26:09.994 --> 26:12.952
and he doesn't understand
what he's just done.

26:13.034 --> 26:16.265
Does that solve my problem?
Answer: No!

26:16.314 --> 26:19.351
Analysis: All we need now
is for someone else...

26:19.434 --> 26:22.028
who understands his capability
to come along...

26:22.074 --> 26:25.225
and my problems are increased
exponentially.

26:25.274 --> 26:28.186
Then maybe we should talk
to the kid.

26:28.274 --> 26:30.583
- And, uh--
- No.

26:31.954 --> 26:34.070
No. No.

26:36.154 --> 26:39.385
There must be nothing
that connects the boy to this office.

26:39.474 --> 26:42.671
Nothing.
Am l clear?

26:42.714 --> 26:44.067
Yes, sir.

26:44.114 --> 26:46.674
l want you to erase
the tape.

26:46.714 --> 26:48.591
Am l clear?

26:49.594 --> 26:51.346
Yes, sir.

26:54.874 --> 26:57.866
- Honey, will you get that?
- Yeah, l got it.

26:58.674 --> 27:00.710
- Martin Lynch?
- Yeah.

27:00.754 --> 27:02.631
Detective Burrell,
Chicago police.

27:02.674 --> 27:05.313
Sorry to bother you. Can l ask you
a few questions? lt's very important.

27:05.394 --> 27:08.466
-l got your address from Simon's school.
-Something wrong?

27:08.554 --> 27:11.307
lf l drag this out,
it's only gonna make things worse.

27:11.394 --> 27:13.589
One of the other parents
has made accusations...

27:13.674 --> 27:16.188
against Simon's driver
of a sexual nature.

27:16.274 --> 27:20.347
- Oh, my God.
- Well, they're only allegations
at this point.

27:20.434 --> 27:22.265
lf l could step inside
and speak with you.

27:22.354 --> 27:24.265
Uh, sure.

27:25.394 --> 27:28.033
lt won't take more
than a moment.

27:30.194 --> 27:33.869
- l don't want to upset you.
- Well, you've already upset us.

27:33.954 --> 27:37.390
- l'm sorry about that.
- Would you like a cup of coffee?

27:37.474 --> 27:39.669
- Or something?
- Yeah. Yeah, that'd be real nice.

28:05.554 --> 28:09.183
911. Emergency operator 562.

28:11.954 --> 28:13.785
911. Emergency operator 562.

28:13.874 --> 28:17.230
What are you reporting?

28:17.274 --> 28:21.153
l have your location on my screen.
Can you tell me what you're reporting?

29:37.274 --> 29:39.469
Anything while l was gone,
Art?

29:39.514 --> 29:42.824
- Yeah, l think we got
a big break in this case.
- What?

29:42.914 --> 29:46.145
The Attorney General herself
just called in 25 dimes on the Cubs.

29:46.194 --> 29:49.231
What do you think?

29:49.274 --> 29:51.151
Uh--

29:54.194 --> 29:56.788
- Yeah?
- This is 13.

29:56.874 --> 29:59.434
- Cubs ten times.
- Got it.

30:02.074 --> 30:05.783
Dumb bet, 13.
Cubs are in a slump.

30:05.874 --> 30:08.468
Would you mind if l told you
something personal?

30:10.754 --> 30:13.393
Yeah, l would, Roger.

30:13.434 --> 30:15.311
l really would.

30:18.234 --> 30:20.111
Excuse me.

30:20.154 --> 30:22.031
Yeah?

30:22.074 --> 30:24.030
Art, for you.

30:25.434 --> 30:27.311
Yeah?

30:27.354 --> 30:30.551
We're sending someone to spell you.
We've got another assignment for you.

30:30.634 --> 30:33.148
Lomax has another matter
of national security for me?

30:33.234 --> 30:35.702
Check into a possible missing child,
2-1 precinct.

30:35.794 --> 30:37.625
Chicago P.D.
retains jurisdiction.

31:11.154 --> 31:14.146
Yeah. Lacerations.

31:14.194 --> 31:16.071
Nichols.

31:16.114 --> 31:18.548
- You still alive?
- Still here, Art.

31:18.634 --> 31:22.513
- How are ya?
- All right.

